9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 134, L.D. 211, “An Act to Make School
10 Safer for Students with Epilepsy and Other Seizure Disorders by Requiring Seizure Action
11 Plans and Training in Schools”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, Directing the Department of Education to Communicate to School
14 Administrative Units and Private Schools the Importance of Adopting Seizure Action
15 Plans'
16 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
17 'Sec. 1. Department of Education to communicate importance of adoption
18 of seizure action plans to school administrative units and approved private
19 schools. Resolved: That the Department of Education shall communicate the importance
20 of the adoption of seizure action plans to school administrative units, as defined in the
21 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 20-A, section 1, subsection 26, and approved private schools
22 as defined in Title 20-A, section 1, subsection 2. The department shall provide information
23 and assistance, if requested, to a school administrative unit or approved private school if
24 the school administrative unit or approved private school requests information or assistance
25 from the department on the adoption of seizure action plans.
26 For the purposes of this resolve, "seizure action plan" means a written, individualized
27 health plan designed to acknowledge and prepare for the health care needs of a student
28 diagnosed with a seizure disorder.'
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment replaces the bill with a resolve. The amendment requires the
3333 Department of Education to communicate the importance of the adoption of seizure action
3344 plans to school administrative units and approved private schools. The department must
